<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-19-0189 </DOCNO><TEXT>The relationship between energy consumption capacities/intensities andsocial development is discussed and Tanzania's current conventional energyresource potential and utilization are reviewed. In the face of uncertainaccess to oil, on which Tanzania is heavily dependent for her commercialenergy, coupled with the high costs involved, the alternative/renewableenergy potentials in the country and possibilities for future energyresearch and development including research in biogas technology andsolar applications are discussed. Some current energy policy issues arehighlighted and possible strategies for overcoming such problems aresuggested.</TEXT></DOC>